01:21:17,620 --> 01:21:22,216
- I told you I was clumsy.
Go on. Taste them.

795
01:21:22,700 --> 01:21:27,728
- They aren't ripe yet.
Leave them in the granary for 3 weeks.

796
01:21:27,940 --> 01:21:29,498
This one.

797
01:21:32,540 --> 01:21:33,939
This one instead.

798
01:21:43,220 --> 01:21:44,778
You're right.

799
01:22:18,620 --> 01:22:19,655
31.

800
01:22:21,380 --> 01:22:22,335
32.

801
01:22:22,780 --> 01:22:25,248
They'll be good in 3 weeks.

802
01:22:25,460 --> 01:22:26,529
Let's hope

803
01:22:28,020 --> 01:22:29,533
I must go home

804
01:22:34,580 --> 01:22:36,013
Did you love Juliette?

805
01:22:36,220 --> 01:22:38,529
Roberte told you the story

806
01:22:38,740 --> 01:22:39,775
Did you love her?

807
01:22:39,980 --> 01:22:41,174
I think so.

808
01:22:41,380 --> 01:22:42,210
and she?

809
01:22:42,420 --> 01:22:44,376
I think she loved me.

810
01:22:44,580 --> 01:22:46,775
And you never saw her again?

811
01:22:46,980 --> 01:22:47,969
No.

812
01:22:48,860 --> 01:22:50,339
She had to suffer

813
01:22:50,540 --> 01:22:52,531
I imagine she suffered.

814
01:22:52,740 --> 01:22:55,174
You never tried to see her again?

815
01:22:55,380 --> 01:22:58,736
- Cowardice is one aspect
of married life.

816
01:22:59,260 --> 01:23:01,455
Why are you married?

817
01:23:01,660 --> 01:23:05,858
- When we got married,
we were no longer in love.

818
01:23:06,060 --> 01:23:08,096
But she was helpless.

819
01:23:08,300 --> 01:23:11,929
I didn't want to save myself
for a bourgeois marriage.

820
01:23:12,140 --> 01:23:17,294
- She should've refused the marraige.
It wasn't her line of safety.

821
01:23:17,500 --> 01:23:22,654
- She has no job. In love,
security comes with age.

822
01:23:24,460 --> 01:23:28,055
- Sometimes the two of you say
some monstrous things.

823
01:23:30,900 --> 01:23:31,650
And Octave?

824
01:23:31,860 --> 01:23:32,929
Octave?

825
01:23:33,980 --> 01:23:35,971
Yeah. The telephone call.

826
01:23:39,420 --> 01:23:40,535
It's true.

827
01:23:43,540 --> 01:23:45,496
I didn't believe it.

828
01:23:45,700 --> 01:23:48,419
Passion has no morals.

829
01:24:04,300 --> 01:24:05,449
I love you.

830
01:24:40,580 --> 01:24:41,899
Good evening, Madame Milan.

831
01:24:42,100 --> 01:24:43,897
Unload the car.

832
01:24:44,100 --> 01:24:46,375
Be careful of the bottles.

833
01:24:51,020 --> 01:24:52,738
I'm late.

834
01:24:52,940 --> 01:24:56,376
There were many of cars
on the highway!

835
01:24:56,580 --> 01:24:57,535
Here.

836
01:24:59,060 --> 01:25:02,496
I wasn't able to find parking
in the prefecture.

837
01:25:04,180 --> 01:25:05,215
Look.

838
01:25:06,940 --> 01:25:10,853
It's a new boy from Paris
It's not bad.

839
01:25:11,060 --> 01:25:14,132
Ah! You know
what I brought back?

840
01:25:15,100 --> 01:25:19,173
A case of scotch. A change from
Radiguette's brandy.

841
01:25:24,620 --> 01:25:25,735
Bargain.

842
01:25:26,580 --> 01:25:29,538
Looks like it came
from a boutique.

843
01:25:32,020 --> 01:25:33,897
You're making a face!

844
01:25:35,540 --> 01:25:36,734
Heartache?

845
01:25:40,940 --> 01:25:41,850
Yes?

846
01:25:42,500 --> 01:25:45,492
Italy? Did you call Italy?

847
01:25:45,860 --> 01:25:49,375
- Yes. I did.
- Thank you Miss, we did.

848
01:25:52,100 --> 01:25:53,852
I called Luigi.

849
01:25:56,260 --> 01:25:59,411
- You called your manager
while on vacation...

850
01:25:59,620 --> 01:26:01,338
My vacation is over.

851
01:26:02,020 --> 01:26:03,009
Is it true?

852
01:26:03,460 --> 01:26:07,738
- I was lucky, a place opened at Ferrari
I was offered a contract.

853
01:26:07,940 --> 01:26:09,419
What position?

854
01:26:09,620 --> 01:26:10,575
The last.

855
01:26:10,780 --> 01:26:14,693
- You can't accept.
They'll pass you off a spare car.

856
01:26:14,900 --> 01:26:18,051
Training starts next week.

857
01:26:18,260 --> 01:26:18,976
At Modena?

858
01:26:19,180 --> 01:26:20,090
Yes.

859
01:26:20,300 --> 01:26:21,733
I do like Modena.

860
01:26:21,940 --> 01:26:23,658
Who says I'm taking you?

861
01:26:23,860 --> 01:26:27,535
- You'll be unhappy
if you have no one to torture.

862
01:26:28,420 --> 01:26:29,739
We'll celebrate.

863
01:26:29,940 --> 01:26:33,933
I almost suspected it:
Because I bought lots of food.

864
01:26:37,740 --> 01:26:40,538
- All preserved food!
You two eat poorly.

865
01:26:40,740 --> 01:26:42,935
It makes up for our drinking.

866
01:26:43,140 --> 01:26:46,974
In fact you don't have to worry
anymore, we're leaving.

867
01:26:47,180 --> 01:26:48,169
Where are you going?

868
01:26:48,380 --> 01:26:50,689
- Milan is back in action,
we're leaving for Italy

869
01:26:50,900 --> 01:26:55,530
- I knew you'd go.
You guys need your fun.

870
01:26:57,060 --> 01:26:58,971
Hйlиne is what worries me.

871
01:26:59,180 --> 01:27:00,169
Why?

872
01:27:01,820 --> 01:27:05,893
- It wouldn't surprise me
if she has a crush on Milan.

873
01:27:07,460 --> 01:27:09,098
You haven't noticed?

874
01:27:09,300 --> 01:27:13,134
When he's not busy with her,
she's ready to cry.

875
01:27:13,340 --> 01:27:17,572
- She's always around
Your stories go straight to her head.

876
01:27:17,780 --> 01:27:18,974
It will pass.

877
01:27:20,260 --> 01:27:24,731
- Yes, but for kids
of that age, it can be serious.

878
01:27:25,940 --> 01:27:28,898
I don't want her
to do something foolish.

879
01:28:16,700 --> 01:28:18,019
What's going on?

880
01:28:18,220 --> 01:28:19,448
We never see you anymore.

881
01:28:19,660 --> 01:28:22,128
- I have work
My exam is approaching.

882
01:28:22,340 --> 01:28:24,012
You're not upset with Milan?

883
01:28:24,220 --> 01:28:25,175
Why?

884
01:28:26,260 --> 01:28:31,414
- Don't blame him.
It's his 40 year equinox.

885
01:28:32,300 --> 01:28:34,860
But what a number with his raven!

886
01:28:35,540 --> 01:28:36,939
I forgot all about it.

887
01:28:37,140 --> 01:28:38,255
You coming for dinner?

888
01:28:38,460 --> 01:28:41,577
- No. Duvel might be coming.
Another time.

889
01:28:41,780 --> 01:28:44,897
- Don't delay if you want
to say goodbye to Milan.

890
01:28:45,100 --> 01:28:45,930
Goodbye?

891
01:28:46,140 --> 01:28:49,610
- You haven't heard the news?
The press had nothing to say?

892
01:28:49,820 --> 01:28:52,334
He's resuming training at Ferrari.

893
01:28:53,180 --> 01:28:55,011
- So we won't see him anymore
around here?

894
01:28:55,220 --> 01:28:58,656
- He's going to race in all the Grand Prix
January in Buenos Aires,..

895
01:28:58,860 --> 01:29:01,852
.. March, Mexico,
April, Monaco.

896
01:29:02,420 --> 01:29:04,092
are you leaving too?

897
01:29:04,300 --> 01:29:08,578
- Like usual, trailing from behind.
To chase away the reporters.

898
01:29:08,780 --> 01:29:12,329
and to handle the hero's
bad moods.

899
01:29:12,540 --> 01:29:16,738
Luigi is coming to sign his contract.
Are you not coming?

900
01:29:17,980 --> 01:29:19,379
Yes I'm coming.

901
01:29:26,780 --> 01:29:29,214
You're sure, you don't regret anything?

902
01:29:29,420 --> 01:29:30,899
Absolutely sure.

903
01:29:32,180 --> 01:29:34,250
You care so much for this girl?

904
01:29:34,460 --> 01:29:36,690
Enough to know what I'm doing.

905
01:29:37,780 --> 01:29:40,248
- And you've never slept with her?
- No.

906
01:29:47,460 --> 01:29:50,975
I love her innocent gaze, her sincerity.

907
01:29:51,180 --> 01:29:54,252
All that wouldn't last
living with me.

908
01:29:54,460 --> 01:29:57,577
One year of crazy love
and 10 years like Roberte and I had

909
01:29:57,780 --> 01:29:59,293
What do you know?

910
01:29:59,500 --> 01:30:02,936
- It's inevitable. I've had
10 years to understand it.

911
01:30:18,700 --> 01:30:19,530
Here!

912
01:30:20,740 --> 01:30:22,776
You're never late!

913
01:30:22,980 --> 01:30:24,174
Dear Roberte!

914
01:30:24,380 --> 01:30:27,531
The country suits you.
- Did you have a good trip?

915
01:30:27,740 --> 01:30:31,779
- I drove all night.
- There's not one minute to lose, is there.

916
01:30:34,660 --> 01:30:36,059
Hйlиne, come!

917
01:30:36,940 --> 01:30:40,330
This is Luigi, the sporting
director of Ferrari.

918
01:30:40,540 --> 01:30:42,258
Hйlиne Morel, our friend.

919
01:30:42,460 --> 01:30:43,415
A pleasure.

920
01:30:43,700 --> 01:30:47,010
- You're going to have dinner with us
and discuss the contract.

921
01:30:47,220 --> 01:30:48,369
But it's been signed.

922
01:30:48,620 --> 01:30:50,895
You took advantage of my absence!

923
01:30:51,100 --> 01:30:55,252
When Milan trusts
someone, he'll sign anything.

924
01:30:55,460 --> 01:30:57,257
But Luigi is a bandit.

925
01:30:57,460 --> 01:31:02,136
- Milan knew very well what he wanted.
I couldn't say a thing.

926
01:31:02,340 --> 01:31:05,696
- You've become a businessman?
- Anything can happen.

927
01:31:05,900 --> 01:31:07,333
When do we leave?

928
01:31:07,780 --> 01:31:10,499
Milan has to be there tomorrow.

929
01:31:10,700 --> 01:31:12,850
I'll go pack quickly

930
01:31:13,060 --> 01:31:17,019
Have you booked our rooms?
- Milan prefers to stay at the factory.

931
01:31:17,220 --> 01:31:20,735
No. They'll talk shop all the time.

932
01:31:20,940 --> 01:31:22,293
He will live alone.

933
01:31:22,500 --> 01:31:23,615
What?

934
01:31:23,900 --> 01:31:26,050
It's in the contract.

935
01:31:26,740 --> 01:31:27,695
And me?

936
01:31:28,220 --> 01:31:29,175
You stay.

937
01:31:31,340 --> 01:31:32,614
Are you kidding?

938
01:31:37,700 --> 01:31:41,898
- Every month, we'll send
you a third of his salary.

939
01:31:58,660 --> 01:31:59,649
You're taking her?

940
01:32:04,460 --> 01:32:05,370
No.

941
01:32:22,180 --> 01:32:27,698
I don't want to start over with her
what we've already done so well.

942
01:33:49,620 --> 01:33:51,338
Get in. I'll take you back.

943
01:34:10,340 --> 01:34:11,659
Take the wheel.

944
01:35:06,620 --> 01:35:07,939
He's gone.

945
01:35:20,780 --> 01:35:22,930
What are you going to do now?

946
01:35:23,940 --> 01:35:25,009
Nothing.

947
01:35:28,180 --> 01:35:32,139
I'll never have the time
to live a great love.

948
01:35:32,340 --> 01:35:33,568
But I love you.

949
01:35:37,540 --> 01:35:38,609
Me too.

950
01:35:45,580 --> 01:35:47,013
You coming?

951
01:35:51,340 --> 01:35:53,490
It's time for dinner.

952
01:35:55,460 --> 01:35:59,009
- It will take a moment.
It won't move. This is troubling.

953
01:35:59,300 --> 01:36:01,370
Maybe we should go there.

954
01:36:01,580 --> 01:36:03,172
Where exactly?

955
01:36:03,380 --> 01:36:06,053
It's on the high road.

956
01:36:06,260 --> 01:36:07,215
It's far.

957
01:36:07,420 --> 01:36:08,773
What's happening?

958
01:36:08,980 --> 01:36:13,576
- He said he saw flames.
- A car that's stuck.

959
01:36:13,780 --> 01:36:16,613
- They won't make it out alone
- Let's go.

960
01:36:16,820 --> 01:36:20,096
We'd better go look Auguste.

961
01:36:20,300 --> 01:36:22,052
Start dinner without me.

962
01:36:59,300 --> 01:37:01,256
We should see the headlights.

963
01:37:01,460 --> 01:37:04,293
- They must have wanted
to save their battery.

964
01:37:31,300 --> 01:37:33,814
They were stuck right here.

965
01:37:35,100 --> 01:37:36,931
They got out alone.

966
01:37:37,140 --> 01:37:40,894
- They had to turn around.
- No the tracks continue.

967
01:37:42,460 --> 01:37:44,178
Where does this path lead?

968
01:37:45,180 --> 01:37:47,899
- It ends abruptly at
the edge of the pond.

969
01:38:06,700 --> 01:38:08,691
But that's the car of...

970
01:38:11,140 --> 01:38:14,894
We must inform Milan.
Where can we place a call to Modena?

971
01:38:37,700 --> 01:38:38,769
Hey, Milan!

972
01:38:41,340 --> 01:38:43,012
Hi, how are you?

973
01:38:43,780 --> 01:38:46,453
You weren't made for the country.

974
01:38:46,660 --> 01:38:48,093
The country is good.

975
01:38:57,300 --> 01:39:00,656
Tell me a little, and Roberte?

976
01:39:00,940 --> 01:39:03,056
Roberte is staying in the village.

977
01:39:03,260 --> 01:39:04,056
Ah?
